An Administration Police Corporal on Monday shot and killed his colleague at Gambela AP Operation Camp in Tigania East, Meru County.The officer fired three bullets killing his colleague on the spot at about 7.40 pm Monday.Tigania East police boss Charles Koskei said they are yet to establish the motive of the killing."Investigation are underway to establish what happened before the officer decided to shoot and kill his colleague. "I was informed the two were at the camp but the corporal suddenly took a gun and shot the other one and he died instantly," said Mr Koskei.The suspect was detained at Muthara Police station while the officer s body was removed to the Meru Teaching and Referral Hospital Mortuary email print email print This will cost the government Sh6,000 per woman and will be loaded onto the NHIF card to be